main event: Multiple unidentified flying object sightings were reported in Trenton, New Jersey, during the years 1955 and 1958, involving radar blips and visual observations.
interesting points: The radar observation from 1958 indicated a blip moving across the screen,The reports classified the sightings as unidentified due to insufficient data,One sighting was specifically noted to be moving near the Moon at a slow, steady pace in 1955,Descriptions of the objects included a general circular shape and a white color,The observers were identified as sincere individuals with an interest in astronomy.
sighted object: Unidentified flying objects detected by radar and visually observed
witness description: A civilian observer familiar with astronomy.
